attachments.fallback: #13485 Inconsistent Label Highlighting for Required Fields
attachments.text:
When creating a new Healthcare Service, the Name field label turns red if left blank, while other required fields (e.g., Location) only show the error message below the input. This causes inconsistency in the UI.

healthcare.mp4 

*Steps to Reproduce*

1. Go to Healthcare Services → Create new.
2. Leave all fields empty.
3. Click Create.

*Expected Behavior*

• All required fields should behave consistently. Labels should remain neutral, and missing input should be indicated only by the error message below the field.

*Actual Behavior*

• Name → Label turns red + error message shown.
• Location → Label stays neutral + error message shown.

Fixes <https://github.com/ohcnetwork/care_fe/issues/13478|#13478>

*Proposed Changes*

• Clear error messages (`setupPasswordError`, `disableError`, `regeneratePasswordError`) when dialogs are closed.
• Ensures a fresh state whenever the user reopens the dialog.
13478.mp4 

Tagging: @ohcnetwork/care-fe-code-reviewers

*Merge Checklist*

• Add specs that demonstrate the bug or test the new feature.
• Update product documentation. (Not applicable for UI alignment changes)
• Ensure that UI text is placed in I18n files.
• Prepare a screenshot or demo video for the changelog entry and attach it to the issue.
• Request peer reviews.
• Complete QA on mobile devices.
• Complete QA on desktop devices.

## Summary by CodeRabbit

• *Bug Fixes*  
   • Two-Factor Authentication password dialogs now clear any error messages when closed across Setup, Disable, and Regenerate flows. This prevents stale errors from persisting when reopening a dialog, ensuring a clean start for each attempt.  
   • Opening behavior is unchanged; only closing the dialog resets errors.  
   • Improves clarity and reduces user confusion during 2FA management without altering existing setup, verification, disable, or regenerate steps.
